<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1659,1956]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,475,1736,1762]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The two dorsal setose lobes on tergite IX and lack of anal point combined with a strongly curved inferior volsella with some apically split setae, and median volsella with strong apical seta will separate the male of 
<taxonomicName box="[446,622,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strebulosum">
<emphasis box="[446,622,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">N. strebulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[798,936,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[798,936,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Nilothauma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
