<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,294]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,321,151,177]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName box="[828,1026,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Paranilothauma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,1026,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Paranilothauma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the two dorsal setose lobes on tergite IX were regarded as belonging to laterosternite IX (
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[831,1093,190,216]" pageId="36" pageNumber="42" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (2000) Paranilothauma strebulosa sp. n. from Costa Rica (Diptera: Chironomidae). In: Hoffrichter, O. (Ed.), Late 20 th Century Research on Chironomidae: An Anthology from the 13 th International Symposium on Chironomidae. Shaker Verlag, Aachen, pp. 19 - 23." type="book chapter" year="2000">
Adam &amp; Saether 
<number box="[1029,1093,190,216]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The addition of several new Neotropical species with similar lobes clearly demonstrates that these lobes originate on tergite IX. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,267,293]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is recorded only from 
<collectingCountry box="[776,907,268,294]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
